Nathanael Abebe

Investment Manager

New York



x

Nathanael Abebe
Investment Manager

Prior to joining Orion, Mr. Abebe worked as a Structured Commodities Trading Analyst at LAMCO LLC, where he valued and executed complex derivatives transactions across the commodities spectrum.  He started his career at Barclays Capital and Lehman Brothers as a Commodities Trading Analyst.  Mr. Abebe earned his BS from Rutgers University in Chemical Engineering and his MBA from the Wharton School (University of Pennsylvania) in Finance.






View Bio


Philip Clegg

Investment Manager

London




x

Philip Clegg
Investment Manager

Prior to Orion, Mr. Clegg spent more than six years at Pala Investments, where he led Pala’s partnerships with their portfolio companies in financial matters, including mergers and acquisitions, capital raising, financial strategy and management. Mr. Clegg also oversaw acquisition finance for new investments and established and managed Pala’s long‐short liquid portfolio. Furthermore, he served as director of Nevada Copper and Chairman of Dumas Mining. Before joining Pala in 2009, Mr. Clegg was a Senior Manager at Deloitte, where he was involved with advisory projects, transactions and consulting engagements in the resource sector. He advised on a number of IPOs, including that of Vedanta Resources, various bond issuances, buy‐side M&A, and consultancy projects. Mr. Clegg graduated from Oxford University with a Masters in Geology. Mr. Clegg is a qualified chartered accountant (ACA).






View Bio


Jonathan Lamb

Investment Manager

New York



x

Jonathan Lamb
Investment Manager

Prior to Orion, Mr. Lamb was an Investment Manager for the Red Kite Group’s Mine Finance business. Before joining Red Kite in 2012, Mr. Lamb worked for five years in Deutsche Bank’s Metals & Mining Investment Banking group.  He was one of the founding members of that team in New York. He has worked on a variety of debt and equity financing as well as M&A transactions for clients across the base metals, precious metals, coal and steel sectors. Mr. Lamb graduated with a BA from the College of William and Mary majoring in Government and Finance.






